3 SECTION 2. IC 21-13-13 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
4 AS A NEW CHAPTER TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
5 JULY 1, 2026]:
6 Chapter 13. Veterinary Medicine Student Loan Repayment
7 Program
8 Sec. 1. For purposes of this chapter, the following definitions
9 apply:
10 (1) "Fund" refers to the veterinary medicine student loan
11 repayment program fund established by section 3 of this
12 chapter.
13 (2) "Program" refers to the veterinary medicine student loan
14 repayment program established by section 2 of this chapter.
15 Sec. 2. (a) The veterinary medicine student loan repayment
16 program is established.
17 (b) The Indiana state board of animal health shall administer
18 the program.
19 Sec. 3. (a) The veterinary medicine student loan repayment
20 program fund is established to provide funds to repay outstanding
21 student loans of:
22 (1) veterinarians; or
23 (2) veterinary technicians;
24 who meet the requirements established by the Indiana state board
25 of animal health.
26 (b) The Indiana state board of animal health shall administer
27 the fund.
28 (c) The fund consists of the following:
29 (1) Appropriations from the general assembly.
30 (2) Grants, including federal grants.
31 (3) Gifts or donations to the Indiana state board of animal
32 health to achieve the purposes of the fund.
33 (4) Interest accrued under subsection (d).
34 (d) The treasurer of state shall invest the money in the fund not
35 currently needed to meet the obligations of the fund in the same
36 manner as other public funds may be invested. Interest that
37 accrues from investments under this subsection must be deposited
38 in the fund.
39 (e) Money in the fund at the end of a state fiscal year does not
40 revert to the state general fund.
41 (f) The expenses of administering the fund may be paid from
42 money in the fund but must not exceed the amounts deposited in
2026 IN 1024—LS 6065/DI 148

3
1 the fund under subsection (c)(1), (c)(2), and (c)(4).
2 (g) A person that provides money to the fund under subsection
3 (c)(3) may direct that the money be used for loan repayments for
4 a specific:
5 (1) veterinarian practice type; or
6 (2) geographic area of Indiana.
7 Sec. 4. The Indiana state board of animal health shall do the
8 following:
9 (1) Establish requirements for the program.
10 (2) Identify individuals who qualify for the program.
11 (3) Determine the amount and duration of the student loan
12 repayment award that an eligible individual receives.
13 (4) Identify areas of need.
14 Sec. 5. (a) To be eligible to receive a student loan repayment
15 award, an individual must meet the following requirements:
16 (1) Apply on a form prescribed by the Indiana state board of
17 animal health.
18 (2) Be a:
19 (A) licensed, accredited veterinarian; or
20 (B) registered veterinarian technician;
21 who is licensed or registered under IC 25-38.1-3.
22 (3) Be a resident of Indiana and a citizen of the United States.
23 (4) Have an outstanding student loan balance from loans
24 secured during professional training at an accredited:
25 (A) college of veterinary medicine; or
26 (B) veterinary technician program.
27 (5) Agree to practice full time in the veterinary profession and
28 provide essential services in Indiana for a specific number of
29 years as determined by the Indiana state board of animal
30 health. When determining essential services in Indiana, the
31 Indiana state board of animal health shall consider the
32 following factors:
33 (A) Rural or other geographic areas of the state that are
34 currently underserved.
35 (B) Food animal or other areas of veterinary practice that
36 are either:
37 (i) currently experiencing; or
38 (ii) projected to experience;
39 a shortage of veterinary practitioners or veterinary
40 technicians.
41 (C) Any other factor that:
42 (i) furthers the protection of human and animal health;
2026 IN 1024—LS 6065/DI 148

4
1 and
2 (ii) ensures the efficient and principled delivery of
3 veterinary medical services in Indiana.
4 (b) The Indiana state board of animal health shall:
5 (1) determine the amount of a student loan repayment award
6 that an eligible individual receives under this chapter; and
7 (2) establish the process for an eligible individual to receive
8 multi-year awards under this chapter.
9 Sec. 6. The Indiana state board of animal health shall transfer
10 student loan repayment awards under this chapter directly to the
11 holder of the eligible individual's outstanding student loans.
12 Sec. 7. The Indiana state board of animal health may make
13 student loan repayment awards to an eligible individual until the
14 balance of the eligible individual's student loans is paid in full.
15 Sec. 8. (a) The Indiana state board of animal health shall
16 prepare a report that includes the following:
17 (1) The receipt, disbursement, and uses of money from the
18 fund.
19 (2) The number of applications submitted for student loan
20 repayment under the program.
21 (3) The number and amount of student loan repayment
22 awards that have been provided.
23 (4) An evaluation of the short term and long term impact of
24 the program on Indiana's delivery of veterinary medical
25 services.
26 (5) Any other information collected concerning the fund,
27 program, or student loan repayments awarded under this
28 chapter.
29 (b) Not later than July 1, 2027, and not later than July 1 every
30 two (2) years thereafter, the Indiana state board of animal health
31 shall submit the report described in subsection (a) to the following:
32 (1) The governor.
33 (2) The general assembly in an electronic format under
34 IC 5-14-6.
35 Sec. 9. The Indiana state board of animal health shall adopt
36 rules under IC 4-22-2 to:
37 (1) establish eligibility requirements to receive student loan
38 repayment awards under the program; and
39 (2) otherwise administer the program.
